@startuml 06-sync-conflict-resolution
title Conflict Resolution Flow (When Sync Enabled)

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    BorderColor #1976D2
}

|Sync Adapter|
start
note right
    **Precondition:**
    Sync must be enabled.
    Local vault always exists
    in IndexedDB (primary).
end note
:Download remote vault (S3);
:Get local vault (IndexedDB);

:Compare timestamps;
note right
    Local: last modified locally
    Remote: from S3 envelope
    LastSync: last successful sync
end note

if (local.modifiedAt > lastSync AND\nremote.timestamp > lastSync) then (CONFLICT)
    :Conflict detected!;
    note right
        Both local and remote
        changed since last sync
        (concurrent edits)
    end note
else (no conflict)
    if (remote.timestamp > local.modifiedAt) then (remote newer)
        :Apply remote changes;
        stop
    else (local newer or equal)
        :Keep local, upload;
        stop
    endif
endif

|Extension UI|
:Show Conflict Dialog;

fork
    :Display Local Version;
    note right
        - Modified timestamp
        - Changed entries
        - Device that made changes
    end note
fork again
    :Display Remote Version;
    note right
        - Signer device ID
        - Timestamp
        - Changed entries
    end note
end fork

:Show Diff View;
note right
    Side-by-side comparison:
    - Added entries (green)
    - Removed entries (red)
    - Modified fields (yellow)
end note

|User|
:Choose Resolution;

switch (User Choice?)
case (Keep Local)
    |Extension|
    :Discard remote;
    :Force upload local;
    :Increment revision;

case (Keep Remote)
    |Extension|
    :Discard local changes;
    :Apply remote vault;
    :Update local storage;

case (Merge)
    |Extension|
    :Field-level merge;
    note right
        **Merge Strategy:**
        - Newer entry wins per-field
        - Deleted items: keep tombstone
        - New items: include both
        - Modified: latest timestamp wins
    end note
    :Create merged vault;
    :Upload merged version;

case (Manual)
    |User|
    :Select entries individually;
    :Confirm selections;
    |Extension|
    :Build custom merge;
    :Upload result;
endswitch

|Extension|
:Update lastSyncTimestamp;
:Clear conflict state;
:Refresh UI;

stop

legend right
    **Conflict Scenarios:**
    1. Same entry edited on 2 devices
    2. Entry deleted on one, edited on other
    3. New entries on both devices (no conflict)
    4. Rollback attack (timestamp < lastSeen)
endlegend

@enduml
